<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Floating non-replaced elements with auto width</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="If width computes to auto then the used value of width is 'shrink-to-fit'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                float: left;
                width: auto;
                height: 96px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                background-color: green;
                border: solid 1px black;
            }
            .c1
            {
                float: left;
                border: solid 1px black;
                width: 96px;
                height: 96px;
                background-color: blue;
            }
            p
            {
                clear: left;
            }
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="c1"></div>
        <div id="d1">Filler Text</div>
        <div class="c1"></div>
        <p>Test passes if no visible white space is between the blue boxes and the green box and the green box is just wide enough to fit the word "Filler Text".</p>
    </body>
</html>